    <!-- Causal Inference -->
    <div class="panel si-discovery-accent-emerald">
      <div class="panel-header">
        <span class="panel-icon">🔗</span>
        <span class="panel-title">CAUSAL INFERENCE — REDSHIFT DRIVES COLOR</span>
      </div>
      <div class="discovery-body">
        <div class="discovery-detail-box discovery-box-emerald">
          Strongest edges: r↔i (0.994), g↔r (0.950), u↔g (0.903)<br>
          do(brightness) → redshift: <strong>NOT significant</strong> ✓<br>
          do(redshift) → brightness: <strong>significant</strong> ✓
        </div>
        <div class="discovery-desc">
          PC/FCI causal discovery on 5,000 SDSS galaxies correctly found that <strong class="color-emerald">redshift causes color changes</strong> (K-correction), not the reverse. Intervention tests (do-calculus) confirmed: artificially changing photometric band brightness has zero causal effect on measured redshift. The system rejected the spurious correlation.
        </div>
        <div class="si-muted-note">
          📡 SDSS DR18 · 🔢 5,000 galaxies · PC + FCI algorithms
        </div>
