        <div class="si-feedback-summary">
          Three feedback loops: <strong>Discovery → Hypothesis</strong> (60% from strong discoveries, strength&gt;0.4) · <strong>Method → Strategy</strong> (50 outcomes tracked, adaptive α) · <strong>Exploration → Coverage</strong> (7/7 sources active, 157 untested pairs mapped)
        </div>
        <div class="discovery-desc">
          ASTRA's Discovery Memory tracks every finding with strength scoring, records which statistical methods succeed per domain, and maps explored vs. unexplored variable pairs. The Adaptive Strategist selects investigation methods by historical success rate (exploration bonus for untested methods). The Hypothesis Generator spawns new hypotheses from strong discoveries, untested variable pairs, and cross-domain structural analogies. <strong class="color-emerald">All three improvement metrics are trending upward</strong> — success rate 76%→100%, significant results per evaluation 1.76→11.12, confidence delta improving.
        </div>
        <div class="discovery-meta">
          <span>🔬 50 method outcomes recorded</span>
          <span>📡 7 data sources explored</span>
          <span>🧬 Top affinity: redshift (3.17)</span>
          <span>🔥 Hot domain: Astrophysics (60.9)</span>
        </div>
